Please listen,

00:20:04.089 --> 00:20:07.089
as Sister Seagrid did tofully explain

00:20:07.089 --> 00:20:10.089
how she learned this lesson.

00:20:10.089 --> 00:20:20.299
World War II was going on.

00:20:21.299 --> 00:20:25.630
Getting worse and worse,

00:20:25.630 --> 00:20:28.630
we got the evacuation notice

00:20:28.630 --> 00:20:30.630
and we had to leave.

00:20:30.630 --> 00:20:38.400
People did terrible things to people.

00:20:38.400 --> 00:20:44.369
They were afraid.

00:20:44.369 --> 00:20:46.369
No matter where you looked,

00:20:46.369 --> 00:20:50.369
there were worldly possessions, material things.

00:20:50.369 --> 00:20:53.369
And everybody threw more things

00:20:53.369 --> 00:20:55.369
and nobody picked anything up.

00:20:55.369 --> 00:20:59.130
But they cared where things

00:20:59.130 --> 00:21:03.130
said would save their life at the moment, something to eat.

00:21:03.130 --> 00:21:10.750
I really didn't know how I would spend my life at that time, right?

00:21:10.750 --> 00:21:15.750
But I knew that I would not use it to get rich,

00:21:15.750 --> 00:21:17.750
to work and work for what?

00:21:17.750 --> 00:21:23.700
I wasn't dedicated to Jehovah at that time.

00:21:23.700 --> 00:21:27.700
Even so, I knew Jehovah wasn't reprieved to him.

00:21:27.700 --> 00:21:33.099
And I'm sure he helped us.

00:21:33.099 --> 00:21:36.099
In 1946, we found out my father was alive

00:21:36.099 --> 00:21:38.099
and my sister was alive.

00:21:38.099 --> 00:21:42.099
We were very privileged to be united as a family.

00:21:42.099 --> 00:21:44.099
And at that time,

00:21:44.099 --> 00:21:47.099
my father was near Berlin.

00:21:47.099 --> 00:21:51.099
And so he started all over again.

00:21:51.099 --> 00:21:53.099
My father, he found a book,

00:21:53.099 --> 00:21:54.099
The Heart of God,

00:21:54.099 --> 00:21:56.099
and started to study the Bible

00:21:56.099 --> 00:21:59.099
with my sister and with myself.

00:21:59.099 --> 00:22:01.099
And little by little,

00:22:01.099 --> 00:22:04.099
he started a congregation at our house.

00:22:04.099 --> 00:22:09.210
Now, coming to know Jehovah,

00:22:09.210 --> 00:22:11.210
learning about the paradise,

00:22:11.210 --> 00:22:14.210
I wanted to tell people about it.

00:22:14.210 --> 00:22:17.210
I knew I would have a purpose in life.

00:22:17.210 --> 00:22:21.099
I heard about Gilead,

00:22:21.099 --> 00:22:24.099
and he said, oh boy, that's where I want to go.

00:22:24.099 --> 00:22:26.099
I wanted to be a missionary.

00:22:26.099 --> 00:22:28.099
I tell the people about the paradise.

00:22:28.099 --> 00:22:33.940
The official ban on the waitresses

00:22:33.940 --> 00:22:37.940
in the eastern zone of Germany came 1950.

00:22:37.940 --> 00:22:39.940
But months before,

00:22:39.940 --> 00:22:42.940
we were already being observed.

00:22:42.940 --> 00:22:47.940
My father got literature for the congregation.

00:22:47.940 --> 00:22:50.940
Many times he would send me on a bicycle

00:22:50.940 --> 00:22:53.940
through the forest with a literature.

00:22:53.940 --> 00:22:57.940
So it's interesting when you're in that situation.

00:22:57.940 --> 00:22:59.940
You might go to prison.

00:22:59.940 --> 00:23:01.940
You just don't worry about it.

00:23:01.940 --> 00:23:03.940
You trust in Jehovah.

00:23:03.940 --> 00:23:05.940
And you just go ahead.

00:23:05.940 --> 00:23:11.410
And that's what our family did.

00:23:11.410 --> 00:23:13.410
Then my father went to the branch

00:23:13.410 --> 00:23:15.410
and they told him,

00:23:15.410 --> 00:23:17.410
Max, there's an assembly in Berlin.

00:23:17.410 --> 00:23:19.410
And if you come,

00:23:19.410 --> 00:23:21.410
don't bring a Bible,

00:23:21.410 --> 00:23:22.410
don't bring a songbook,

00:23:22.410 --> 00:23:23.410
bring nothing.

00:23:23.410 --> 00:23:25.410
So, when my father came back

00:23:25.410 --> 00:23:26.410
from that meeting,

00:23:26.410 --> 00:23:27.410
he told us,

00:23:27.410 --> 00:23:28.410
and he said, well,

00:23:28.410 --> 00:23:30.410
if we go,

00:23:30.410 --> 00:23:35.140
it looks like we can't come back.

00:23:35.140 --> 00:23:37.140
So I said, I'm going.

00:23:37.140 --> 00:23:39.140
And my mother said, I'm going.

00:23:39.140 --> 00:23:41.140
So we all made up our mind.

00:23:41.140 --> 00:23:42.140
We would go.

00:23:42.140 --> 00:23:44.140
That means we would get prepared

00:23:44.140 --> 00:23:46.140
to leave everything again, right?

00:23:46.140 --> 00:23:48.140
So I just put one dress

00:23:48.140 --> 00:23:49.140
on top of the other,

00:23:49.140 --> 00:23:51.140
took the bicycle and I'll be right.

00:23:51.140 --> 00:23:57.140
Shortly after we left,

00:23:57.140 --> 00:23:59.140
a police car came

00:23:59.140 --> 00:24:01.140
and they looked for us.

00:24:01.140 --> 00:24:10.000
It was a special arrangement

00:24:10.000 --> 00:24:12.000
and privilege to be

00:24:12.000 --> 00:24:14.000
at a convention in Berlin.

00:24:14.000 --> 00:24:16.000
So we all thanked Jehovah

00:24:16.000 --> 00:24:18.000
that we were there to listen to

00:24:18.000 --> 00:24:19.000
and be strengthened

00:24:19.000 --> 00:24:21.000
that spiritual food.

00:24:21.000 --> 00:24:26.230
And after the convention,

00:24:26.230 --> 00:24:31.230
we were recognized as refugees.

00:24:31.230 --> 00:24:33.230
Got out on a plane

00:24:33.230 --> 00:24:35.230
to West Germany.

00:24:35.230 --> 00:24:37.230
My father said, well,

00:24:37.230 --> 00:24:39.230
now here, for the second time,

00:24:39.230 --> 00:24:41.230
we lost all the material things

00:24:41.230 --> 00:24:43.230
we had in Germany here.

00:24:43.230 --> 00:24:45.230
So we better immigrate

00:24:45.230 --> 00:24:46.230
to the United States

00:24:46.230 --> 00:24:47.230
where my sister was,

00:24:47.230 --> 00:24:49.230
that we all would be together.

00:24:49.230 --> 00:24:50.230
And I said, good,

00:24:50.230 --> 00:24:52.230
I get close to Gilead.

00:24:52.230 --> 00:24:56.730
And then I was privileged

00:24:56.730 --> 00:25:00.730
to attend the 29th class of Gilead.

00:25:00.730 --> 00:25:04.730
And my assignment was Brazil.

00:25:04.730 --> 00:25:07.730
And it was like paradise.

00:25:07.730 --> 00:25:11.579
And there,

00:25:11.579 --> 00:25:12.579
I met my husband

00:25:12.579 --> 00:25:14.579
who was my circuit overseer.

00:25:14.579 --> 00:25:17.829
And so I was privileged

00:25:17.829 --> 00:25:18.829
to travel with him.

00:25:18.829 --> 00:25:21.829
That was a great, great blessing.

00:25:21.829 --> 00:25:28.099
All money can pay for the blessings I have.

00:25:28.099 --> 00:25:33.019
Life is the most important thing there is

00:25:33.019 --> 00:25:35.019
because no matter how much you have,

00:25:35.019 --> 00:25:38.019
you can't prolong your life.

00:25:38.019 --> 00:25:40.019
And then learning about Jehovah

00:25:40.019 --> 00:25:41.019
who gave his son

00:25:41.019 --> 00:25:44.019
to safest from all those terrible things.

00:25:44.019 --> 00:25:47.019
Why wouldn't you use your life

00:25:47.019 --> 00:25:48.019
to serve him?

00:25:48.019 --> 00:25:53.670
Trust in Jehovah.

00:25:53.670 --> 00:25:55.670
And do what you can do

00:25:55.670 --> 00:25:57.670
to serve him from your heart.

00:25:57.670 --> 00:26:02.369
He will never leave you.

