When the fighting got closer,

00:26:27.380 --> 00:26:29.380
we hit.

00:26:29.380 --> 00:26:32.380
But I'm not sure how much longer we can stay here.

00:26:32.380 --> 00:26:36.589
Some in the congregation

00:26:36.589 --> 00:26:38.589
plan to leave the country.

00:26:38.589 --> 00:26:40.589
Mother says we'll try to

00:26:40.589 --> 00:26:42.589
when the shelling comes down.

00:26:42.589 --> 00:26:45.589
But it feels like it may never stop.

00:26:45.589 --> 00:26:48.589
Jehovah, can you still see us?

00:26:48.589 --> 00:26:51.589
Luda, you can finish this.

00:26:51.589 --> 00:26:57.559
We have a little more.

00:26:57.559 --> 00:26:59.559
Always writing like your father.

00:26:59.559 --> 00:27:01.559
Thank you, Grandma.

00:27:01.559 --> 00:27:10.799
You're worried about our brothers and sisters.

00:27:11.799 --> 00:27:14.799
Do you remember the day's text?

00:27:14.799 --> 00:27:16.799
No weapon formed against you

00:27:16.799 --> 00:27:18.799
will have any success.

00:27:18.799 --> 00:27:22.049
That's right.

00:27:22.049 --> 00:27:24.049
When we were under ban,

00:27:24.049 --> 00:27:28.049
Satan did everything to break our faith

00:27:28.049 --> 00:27:30.049
for decades.

00:27:30.049 --> 00:27:32.049
But he couldn't stop us preaching.

00:27:32.049 --> 00:27:35.650
You know why?

00:27:35.650 --> 00:27:36.650
No.

00:27:36.650 --> 00:27:38.650
Nothing can take Jehovah's law

00:27:38.650 --> 00:27:40.650
away from his people.

00:27:40.650 --> 00:27:42.650
They tried.

00:27:42.650 --> 00:27:46.990
But we just threw closer to him.

00:27:46.990 --> 00:27:49.990
Jehovah cared for us then.

00:27:49.990 --> 00:27:51.990
And he still does.

00:27:51.990 --> 00:27:54.990
Even if we lose our lives,

00:27:54.990 --> 00:27:57.990
that weapon will have no success

00:27:57.990 --> 00:28:11.700
because of the resurrection.

00:28:11.700 --> 00:28:14.700
Luda, it's time.

00:28:14.700 --> 00:28:17.700
We have to go now.

00:28:17.700 --> 00:28:27.750
It took forever to get to the station.

00:28:27.750 --> 00:28:30.750
One by one, trains left the city.

00:28:30.750 --> 00:28:35.160
There were so many people.

00:28:35.160 --> 00:28:38.160
So much fear.

00:28:38.160 --> 00:28:40.160
Many of the brothers were arrested

00:28:40.160 --> 00:28:42.160
because they would not fight.

00:28:42.160 --> 00:28:44.160
But a few were with us.

00:28:44.160 --> 00:28:46.160
The soldier will need to see your IDs.

00:28:46.160 --> 00:28:50.109
Let's make a line.

00:28:50.109 --> 00:28:53.109
Hours felt like days.

00:28:53.109 --> 00:28:55.109
I didn't know if we would get on.

00:28:55.109 --> 00:29:10.230
There's no more room from you back

00:29:10.230 --> 00:29:20.529
to the shelter now.

00:29:20.529 --> 00:29:22.529
We can try again tomorrow.

00:29:23.529 --> 00:29:38.849
Luda, Jehovah will care for us.

00:29:38.849 --> 00:29:41.849
This is just a delay, not a defeat.

00:29:41.849 --> 00:29:47.049
Come, please.

00:29:47.049 --> 00:29:49.049
I'll have to go check on the others.

00:29:49.049 --> 00:30:08.589
But I'll text you the moment we know more.

00:30:08.589 --> 00:30:11.589
What are you thinking about?

00:30:11.589 --> 00:30:14.589
I wish Papa were here with us.

00:30:14.589 --> 00:30:17.589
I know you do.

00:30:17.589 --> 00:30:20.589
Your father knew you so well.

00:30:20.589 --> 00:30:24.579
I miss them too.

00:30:24.579 --> 00:30:27.859
What hurts?

00:30:27.859 --> 00:30:29.859
I think of Jehovah's special promise

00:30:29.859 --> 00:30:32.859
to care for us.

00:30:32.859 --> 00:30:36.549
Do you remember?

00:30:36.549 --> 00:30:39.549
Yes.

00:30:39.549 --> 00:30:42.549
Psalms 68.5.

00:30:42.549 --> 00:30:47.630
A father of the fatherless.

00:30:47.630 --> 00:30:51.259
I want to trust him.

00:30:51.259 --> 00:30:56.750
You can.

00:30:56.750 --> 00:30:58.750
The trains have stopped.

00:30:58.750 --> 00:31:00.750
Sheldon destroyed some of the tracks.

00:31:00.750 --> 00:31:02.750
What?

00:31:02.750 --> 00:31:03.750
Are we trapped?

00:31:03.750 --> 00:31:09.880
Don't worry, dear.

00:31:09.880 --> 00:31:11.880
But we just know we are here.

00:31:11.880 --> 00:31:14.880
Jehovah won't forget us.

00:31:14.880 --> 00:31:16.880
Let's pray.

00:31:16.880 --> 00:31:31.640
We're here.

00:31:31.640 --> 00:31:34.640
We're over here.

00:31:34.640 --> 00:31:36.640
I'm sorry, it took so long.

00:31:36.640 --> 00:31:38.640
Did you hear about the trains?

00:31:38.640 --> 00:31:41.640
Don't worry. There is good news.

00:31:41.640 --> 00:31:45.460
We couldn't leave.

00:31:45.460 --> 00:31:48.460
But brothers and sisters in a safe part of the city

00:31:48.460 --> 00:31:51.460
opened their homes to us.

00:31:52.460 --> 00:31:55.460
I learned that a war can't stop Jehovah.

00:31:55.460 --> 00:31:59.460
He'll always find a way to care for his people.

00:31:59.460 --> 00:32:03.700
Nothing can take Jehovah's love away.

00:32:03.700 --> 00:32:09.490
I don't know where he will guide us.

00:32:09.490 --> 00:32:11.490
But I trust him.

00:32:11.490 --> 00:32:20.019
Luda trusted in Jehovah

00:32:20.019 --> 00:32:26.019
and was not overreached by fear or discouragement.

